@database DC240_Rexx.guide

@master DC240_Rexx.guide
@node main
@title "Available commands"

The following ARexx commands are available for DC240_Tool.


@{b}@{u}Program Control@{uu}@{ub}

@{"SER_DEVICE " link "SER_DEVICE"}  NAME
@{"THUMB_DIR  " link "THUMB_DIR"}  DIRECTORY
@{"SER_UNIT   " link "SER_UNIT"}  UNIT
@{"BAUD       " link "BAUD"}  9600/S,19200/S,38400/S,57600/S,115200/S
@{"PACKET_SIZE" link "PACKET_SIZE"}  512/S,1024/S,2048/S,4096/S,8192/S,16384/S,32768/S
@{"QUIT       " link "QUIT"}


@{b}@{u}Camera Control@{uu}@{ub}

@{"ZOOM       " link "ZOOM"}  LEVEL/N
@{"TAKE_PIC   " link "TAKE_PIC"}

@{b}@{u}Camera Status@{uu}@{ub}

@{"CAMERA_NAME" link "CAMERA_NAME"}  NAME
@{"CARD_NAME  " link "CARD_NAME"}
@{"FIRMWARE   " link "FIRMWARE"}
@{"MICRO_8    " link "MICRO_8"}
@{"MICRO_32   " link "MICRO_32"}
@{"PICS_TAKEN " link "PICS_TAKEN"}
@{"FLASH_FIRED" link "FLASH_FIRED"}
@{"SPACE_LO   " link "SPACE_LO"}
@{"SPACE_MED  " link "SPACE_MED"}
@{"SPACE_HI   " link "SPACE_HI"}
@{"LAST_PIC   " link "LAST_PIC"}


@{b}@{u}Image Control@{uu}@{ub}

@{"QUALITY    " link "QUALITY"}  BEST/S,BETTER/S,GOOD/S
@{"FLASH_MODE " link "FLASH_MODE"}  AUTO/S,FILL/S,OFF/S,REDEYE/S 
@{"SHARPNESS  " link "SHARPNESS"}  SOFT/S,NORMAL/S,SHARP/S
@{"FOCUS      " link "FOCUS"}  AUTO/S,CLOSE/S,INFINITY/S
@{"EXPOSURE   " link "EXPOSURE"}  AUTO/S,CENTRE/S
@{"WHITE_BAL  " link "WHITE_BAL"}  AUTO/S,FLUORESCENT/S,TUNGSTEN/S,DAYLIGHT/S
@{"IMAGE_SIZE " link "IMAGE_SIZE"}  640/S,1280/S


@{b}@{u}Storage Control@{uu}@{ub}

@{"CD         " link "CD"}  NAME
@{"DIR        " link "DIR"}  RESULT/A
@{"DELETE_PIC " link "DELETE_PIC"}  PICNAME/A
@{"READ_PIC   " link "READ_PIC"}  PICNAME/A,DEST/A
@{"PROTECT    " link "PROTECT"}  PICNAME/A,OFF/S,ON/S

@endnode

@node "SER_DEVICE"

SER_DEVICE on its own reads the currently selected AmigaDOS device for
communication with the camera.

SER_DEVICE <Device Name> changes the device. Any serial-type device should
work. Note that the program will need to be restarted to use the new device.

On completion, RC contains a resultcode; RESULT contains the currently selected
device.

@endnode

@node "SER_UNIT"

SER_UNIT on its own reads the currently selected unit of the AmigaDOS device
set for communication with the camera.

SER_UNIT <Unit number> changes the device unit number. Note that the program
will need to be restarted to use the new device.

On completion, RC contains a resultcode; RESULT contains the currently selected
unit.

@endnode

@node "BAUD"

BAUD on its own reads the currently selected baud rate set for communication
with the camera.

BAUD <Rate> changes the baud rate. Only the following options are valid:

     9600, 19200, 38400, 57600, 115200

On completion, RC contains a resultcode; RESULT contains the currently selected
rate.

@endnode

@node "ZOOM"

ZOOM on its own reads the current zoom level.

ZOOM <amount> sets the camera's zoom level. Valid values range from 100 to 600
percent.

/* Example */

ADDRESS "DC240MUI.1"
OPTIONS RESULTS

ZOOM 500
if RC then
  say "Problem setting zoom!"
else
  say "Zoom now set to 500%."

@endnode

@node "CAMERA_NAME"

CAMERA_NAME on its own returns the camera's identity string in the RESULT
variable.

CAMERA_NAME <New Name> changes the camera's ID.

On completion, RC contains the result code and RESULT contains the camera's ID
string.

@endnode

@node "CARD_NAME"

CARD_NAME returns the camera's identity string in the RESULT variable.

On completion, RC contains the result code and RESULT contains the currently
inserted card's ID string. This can only be set when the card is formatted.

@endnode

@node "FIRMWARE"

FIRMWARE returns the camera's firmware version number in the RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "MICRO_8"

MICRO_8 returns the camera's 8-bit microprocessor revision number in the RESULT
variable.

@endnode

@node "MICRO_32"

MICRO_32 returns the camera's 32-bit microprocessor revision number in the
RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "PICS_TAKEN"

PICS_TAKEN returns the total number of pictures taken with this camera in the
RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "FLASH_FIRED"

FLASH_FIRED returns the total number of times the flash has been used on this
camera in the RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "SPACE_LO"

SPACE_LO returns the estimated number of pictures at low resolution that would
fit in the remaining memory in the RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "SPACE_MED"

SPACE_MED returns the estimated number of pictures at medium resolution that
would fit in the remaining memory in the RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "SPACE_HI"

SPACE_HI returns the estimated number of pictures at high resolution that
would fit in the remaining memory in the RESULT variable.

@endnode

@node "LAST_PIC"

LAST_PIC returns the name of the most recently taken picture in the RESULT
variable. If no pictures have been taken since power-on, RC is set to 1 and
RESULT is undefined.

@endnode

@node "TAKE_PIC"

TAKE_PIC instructs the camera to take a picture using the current settings.
This command may take several seconds to return since it waits for the camera
to take @{i}and process@{ui} the picture.

On completion, RC contains a result code.

@endnode

@node "PACKET_SIZE"

PACKET_SIZE on its own reads the currently selected packet size set for communication
with the camera. The larger the packet, the more prone to errors it is.

PACKET_SIZE <Size> changes the packet size. Only the following options are
valid:

     512, 1024, 2048, 4096, 8192, 16384, 32768

On completion, RC contains a resultcode; RESULT contains the currently selected
size.

@endnode

@node "QUIT"

Simply quits the program.

@endnode

@node "THUMB_DIR"

THUMB_DIR on its own reads the currently selected storage directory for
thumbnail pictures.

THUMB_DIR <Directory> changes the thumbnail storage directory to the specified
one.

On completion, RC contains a resultcode; RESULT contains the currently selected
directory.


/* Example */

ADDRESS "DC240MUI.1"
OPTIONS RESULTS

THUMB_DIR
say "Current thumb directory is " || RESULT

THUMB_DIR "RAM:"
if RC then
  say "Error changing directory!"
else
  say "New dir is " || RESULT

@endnode

@node "QUALITY"

QUALITY on its own returns the currently selected image quality setting in the
RESULT variable.

QUALITY <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     BEST, BETTER, GOOD

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "FLASH_MODE"

FLASH_MODE on its own returns the currently selected flash setting in the RESULT
variable.

FLASH_MODE <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     AUTO, FILL, OFF, REDEYE

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "SHARPNESS"

SHARPNESS on its own returns the currently selected image sharpness setting in
the RESULT variable.

SHARPNESS <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     SOFT, NORMAL, SHARP

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "FOCUS"

FOCUS on its own returns the currently selected focussing mode in the RESULT
variable.

FOCUS <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     AUTO, CLOSE, INFINITY

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "EXPOSURE"

EXPOSURE on its own returns the currently selected exposure measuring mode in
the RESULT variable.

EXPOSURE <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     AUTO, CENTRE

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "WHITE_BAL"

WHITE_BAL on its own returns the currently selected white balance setting in the
RESULT variable.

WHITE_BAL <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     AUTO, FLUORESCENT, TUNGSTEN, DAYLIGHT

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "IMAGE_SIZE"

IMAGE_SIZE on its own returns the currently selected image size setting in the
RESULT variable.

IMAGE_SIZE <mode> changes the current setting. The following values are accepted:

     640, 1280

On completion, RC contains a resultcode and RESULT contains the current
setting.

@endnode

@node "CD"

CD on its own returns the camera's current directory within the memory card.

CD <name> attempts to change the current directory to the one specified. The
root directory is '/'. Either DOS-style ('\\') or Amiga/Unix style ('/')
directory separators are supported.

Relative or absolute paths may be used. Unix-style directory navigation is
used; that is, '.' is the current directory and '..' is the parent.

If the path is correct, RC will contain 0 and RESULT will contain the new
current directory. If the path is not correct, RC will contain 1.

/* Example */

ADDRESS "DC240MUI.1"
OPTIONS RESULTS

CD
say "Current directory is " || RESULT

CD "/"    /* Change to the root */
if RC then do
  say "Problem changing to '/'!"
  exit
end
else say "Now in '/'"

CD "DCIM\\100DC240"    /* Change into an image directory */
if RC then do
  say "Problem changing to 'DCIM\100DC240'!"
  exit
end

CD ".."  /* Change back to the parent directory */

CD "/DCIM/100DC240"   /* Change back to the image directory from anywhere */

@endnode

@node "DIR"

DIR <VAR> returns information about the contents of the current camera
directory in the named variable.

/* Example */

ADDRESS "DC240MUI.1"
OPTIONS RESULTS

CD "/DCIM/100DC240"
if RC THEN DO
  say "Can't find image directory"
  exit
end

DIR MyFiles
if ~RC THEN DO
  say MyFiles "Entries:"
  i = 1
  do while (i <= MyFiles)
    if MyFiles.i.Type = "Dir" then MyFiles.i.Type = "Dir "
    say i "<" || MyFiles.i.Type || ">" MyFiles.i
    i = i + 1
  END
END
ELSE say "Didn't retrieve the directory"

@endnode

@node "DELETE_PIC"

DELETE_PIC <Picture> attempts to delete the picture named from the camera's
memory card.

On completion, RC contains a resultcode.

@endnode

@node "READ_PIC"

READ_PIC <Picture_Name> <File_Name> attempts to read the named picture from the
camera into the local file specified. This command can take several seconds to
return, during which the ARexx program and DC240_Tool will not respond to
input.

If the transfer is successful, RC will contain 0 else RC will contain 1.

@endnode

@node "PROTECT"

PROTECT <Picture> <OFF | ON> changes the protection on the named picture on the
camera's memory card. DC240_Tool's thumbnail display is not automatically
updated by this command; you can use 'CD "."' to refresh the current directory
display.

RC is set to show success or failure.

@endnode
